Waste Management
​
Trash and Recycling
Trash days are Tuesday and Friday. Recyclables are Fridays only
. Please remember to bring covered trash containers and recycle carts to the edge of your driveway no earlier than the evening before the trash pickup and recycling days (6 p.m. or later). All trash must be in containers with lid securely fastened-- loose garbage bags are not permitted.
Bulk Pickup:
For bulk pickup, call Waste Management at 772-546-7700
​
Recycling Cart Use
Be sure to "Recycle Right" by including clean, dry and empty cardboard, paper,
bottles and cans in your recycling bins. DO NOT place plastic bags, clothing, batteries
or flammable items in your recycling bins.
To request a Recycle Tote, call Waste Management at  (772) 546-7700.
For more information, visit
www.martin.fl.us/Garbage-Recycling-Yard-Waste
Yard Debris Day
Wednesdays are the only day for yard debris pickup. Please remember to place yard debris at the curbside of your property; not in the street, no earlier than Tuesday evening (the night before pickup day).
​
HOLIDAY SCHEDULE
If a holiday falls on a weekday, residential collection will be delayed one day for the remainder of the week. For example: If the holiday falls on Monday, then Monday's collection will be on Tuesday. The one-day delay will occur for each day of the week. If a holiday falls on a Saturday or Sunday, there will be NO delays.
​

JBCC HOA Website Management
This website is managed by the Communications Committee of the Jensen Beach Country Club Homeowners' Association. Committee members are homeowner volunteers.
​
The committee welcomes feedback and suggestions for existing and new content as well as reporting of broken links, incorrect content, and/or spelling and grammatical errors.
Please direct all comments to the Communications Committee chair,
Walt Mitton
